dependencies.description:
GNU Make is a tool which controls the generation of executables and
other non-source files of a program from the program's source files.
dependencies.name: gmake

description:
Http_post does a POST operation to an HTTP URL and dumps the results to
stdout. It does not do gopher, ftp, file, news, or any other type of
URL, only HTTP. It can be configured to do HTTPS POSTs as well.
name: http-post

variants.name: build_system
